findings.suggestion:
BEFORE:
if (schemaDescription.includes('persons')) {
  return this.entityResponse as T
}
return this.activityResponse as T

AFTER:
private callIndex = 0

async generateStructured<T>(): Promise<T> {
  // First call extracts entities, second classifies activity
  return (this.callIndex++ === 0
    ? this.entityResponse
    : this.activityResponse) as T
}

WHY: Call-order dispatch is coupled to the merger's call sequence (documented in the merger), not to fragile string content. If the schema description wording changes, the test still works correctly.
